article.headline: Gottstein typifies efficient Eagles in romp
article.linkText: Hot-shooting Boston College has easy time with Pitt
article.story:
PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Becky Gottstein scored 18 of her 23 points in
the first half Saturday, leading Boston College (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No. 24 AP) to a 78-52
rout of Pittsburgh.

	   Gottstein made six of her first eight shots as Boston College
(18-6, 10-3 Big East) built a 21-6 lead in the first eight minutes.

	   Jessalyn Deveny finished with 20 points and 10 rebounds for the
Eagles. Laine Selwyn led the Panthers with 18 points and Haley
Harguth added 15.

	   The Panthers (11-13, 3-10) shot 32 percent and had only six
assists. The Eagles shot 50 percent.

	   Pittsburgh trailed 26-16 in the first half. The Panthers cut the
lead to 44-31 on Selwyn's fast-break layup with 15:18 remaining,
but Boston College built a 76-45 lead with 2:45 left.
